name: Castle Fine Art, Windsor
address: Unit 24, Windsor Royal Station, Jubilee Arch, Windsor SL4 1PJ, United Kingdom
description:
The UK's leading limited edition print and original art retailer, with international delivery and galleries nationwide.

Home to Windsor Castle, this historic town also has links to William the Conquerer. So it was only right that our gallery's esteemed collection of original and limited edition art was housed somewhere suitably noble.
Our artspace in Windsor Royal Station regularly hosts artist appearances and exhibitions and is located just a short walk from Windsor & Eton Central railway station.

description:
Bringing Artists and Art lovers together since 2005, the family-friendly annual Windsor Art Fair is held in November. Over 5,000 original works of art on sale direct from the Artist or their representing gallery. Affordable, genuine contemporary art in different genres and media. Live art demonstrations, workshops and more.
Contemporary Art Fairs run the Windsor Art Fair along with sister Art Fairs in Surrey, Newbury and Harrogate.
Miniature paintings from PS50 to fine art photography, paintings and sculpture for sale.

name: Art Windsor-Essex
address: 401 Riverside Dr W, Windsor, ON N9A 7J1, Canada
description: Art Windsor-Essex (AWE) supports the presentation of Canadian visual arts in the international border community of Windsor-Detroit, one of the busiest border crossings in North America. Established in 1943 the Gallery is a cultural pillar situated in a premium downtown riverfront location overlooking the Detroit River and downtown skylines. The Gallery is known for its cutting-edge contemporary art program and Canadian art collection of nearly 4,000 works. The Gallery has received 20 organizational awards since 2013, including being the recipient of the Best of Windsor Award for Best Public Art Gallery or Public Art Space.
